description:
In episode 733, Jack and Miles are joined by Ethnically Ambiguous co-host Shereen Younes to discuss Trumps comments on the election, the Kamala Harris and Mike Pence debate, the white terrorists planning on kidnapping Gretchen Whitmer, Ron DeSantis trying to kill Florida, Dreams going to number one on the charts, what we're watching for Monday, and more!

FOOTNOTES:

  1. "We shouldn't be hurting our workers because China put the curse on" -- Trump is now accusing China of putting a "curse" on the US
  2. "Unless Bill Barr indicts these people for crimes -- the greatest political crime in history of our country -- then we'll get little satisfaction ... and that includes Obama and that includes Biden" -- Trump calls for Obama and Biden to be charged with crimes
  3. Trump is ranting and raving about indicting Hillary Clinton
  4. Trump refers to Kamala Harris as "this monster"
  5. Six Takeaways From the Vice-Presidential Debate
  6. Plans to kidnap Whitmer, overthrow government spoiled, officials say
  7. Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis Won’t Stop Dolphins From Packing 65,000 Seat Stadium
  8. Fleetwood Mac’s TikTok-fueled Renaissance, by the Numbers
  9. WATCH: The Budos Band - The Wrangler
